ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Weekly summary of interdaily stability at rest
Notes: Quantifies the synchronization to the 24 hour light�dark cycle. IS is related to sleep quality, cognitive, behavioral and emotional functioning

ElementDescription: Weekly summary of  interdaily stability while active
Notes: Quantifies the synchronization to the 24 hour light�dark cycle. IS is related to sleep quality, cognitive, behavioral and emotional functioning

ElementDescription: Weekly summary of  intradaily variability at rest
Notes: IV serves as a marker of sleep-wake cycle disturbances

ElementDescription: Weekly summary of  intradaily variability while active
Notes: IV serves as a marker of sleep-wake cycle disturbances

ElementDescription: Weekly Average movement during active part of the day
Notes: Level of activity in given time period

ElementDescription: Weekly Standard deviation of movement during active part of the day
Notes: Level of activity in given time period

ElementDescription: Weekly Average movement at rest
Notes: Level of activity in given time period

ElementDescription: Weekly Standard deviation of movement at rest
Notes: Level of activity in given time period

ElementDescription: Weekly average circadian Rhythm Strength
Weekly standard deviation of  circadian Rhythm Strength
Weekly average rest start index in hour
Weekly standard deviation of rest start index in hour
Weekly mean Mesor
Weekly standard deviation of Mesor
Weekly mean amplitude during Cosinor-base Rhythmometry
Weekly standard deviation of amplitude during Cosinor-base Rhythmometry
Weekly mean acrophase during Cosinor-base Rhythmometry
Weekly standard deviation of acrophase during Cosinor-base Rhythmometry
Daily Rest start index (RSI)
Notes: Hour index of the start of rest region.

ElementDescription: Daily average mesor
Notes: 24 hour rhythm-adjusted mean of activity movements

ElementDescription: Daily average Circadian Rhythm Strength (CRS)
Notes: Strength of the rest/activity cycle measured as ratio of average movement in active part of the day to average movement during rest.

ElementDescription: Daily average amplitude
Notes: Measure of the extent of rhythmic change or range of activity and rest values over 24 hours

ElementDescription: Daily average acrophase
Notes: Time of the peak in the 24 hour cycle; measure of the timing of overall high values recurring in each cycle
